Here is an nice summary of a variety of wireless data products:

http://hydra.carleton.ca/info/wlan.html

I have used metricom modems to control robots and have had good success
with them. They are not terribly inexpensive but work well and have a link
budget sufficient to cover reasonable distances, include some degree of
building penetration. 


-Matt


